b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48351.htm)  [Next](sbe48353.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n8\\. Hence the awaking from that.\n\nSince Brahman alone directly is the place of deep sleep, Scripture is able to\ndeclare that the souls awake from that, i.e. Brahman; compare 'Having come\nback from the True they do not know that they come from the True' ( _Kh_. Up.\nVI, io, 2), and other texts.--Here terminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'the\nabsence of that.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 9. But the same, on account of work, remembrance, text, and\ninjunction](sbe48353.htm)\n\n"